# Øgreid AS — Visual Design Manual

> **Read this file BEFORE creating any branded content for Øgreid AS.**
> This is the single source of truth for Øgreid's visual identity.

## Colors

The canonical color definitions are maintained in **`brand-colors.json`** in the GitHub repository.
Fetch the latest version: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ornhalvorsen/odf/main/brand-colors.json`

## Asset Quick Reference

**GitHub repository:** [ornhalvorsen/odf](https://github.com/ornhalvorsen/odf)
**Raw file base URL:** `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ornhalvorsen/odf/main/`

To download any asset, append its path to the base URL. For example:
`https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ornhalvorsen/odf/main/logos/symbol.png`

All assets live in this repository at the root level. Use these paths directly.

```
logos/
├── symbol.png              ← Red 3-house icon (digital)
├── symbol.jpg
├── wordmark-black.png      ← "ØGREID" text (light backgrounds)
├── wordmark-black.jpg
├── wordmark-white.png      ← "ØGREID" text (dark backgrounds)
└── logo-with-clearspace.png
illustrations/               ← Transparent backgrounds (preferred)
├── hero.png                ← Main visual / opening
├── people.png              ← Team / culture
├── history.png             ← Heritage / timeline
├── humor-1.png             ← Light-hearted 1
├── humor-2.png             ← Light-hearted 2
├── collaboration.png       ← Partnerships / intro
├── network.png             ← Connections / ecosystem
├── sparring.png            ← Advisory / mentoring
└── growth-capital.png      ← Investment / growth
illustrations-bg/            ← Same set, WITH background fill
└── (same filenames)
banners/
├── banner-1.png
├── banner-2.png
├── linkedin-1-hd.png
└── linkedin-2-hd.png
anniversary/
└── 150-years.jpg            ← 2026 anniversary illustration
```

---

## 1. Brand Overview

Øgreid AS is an active investor and company developer based in Stavanger, Norway, with roots going back to 1876. In 2026, Øgreid celebrates its **150th anniversary**. The brand tone is confident, warm, approachable, and long-term oriented. The visual identity balances heritage with modern, clean design.

**Address:** Løkkeveien 59, 4008 Stavanger
**Website:** ogreid.no
**Design by:** Studio Oker
**Illustrations by:** Åge Peterson

---

## 2. Color Palette

> **Source of truth:** `brand-colors.json` in the repository. The tables below are a human-readable summary.
> If values differ, `brand-colors.json` wins.

### Primary Colors

| Name | Hex | RGB | Usage |
|------|-----|-----|-------|
| **Øgreid Red** | `#BE4642` | `rgb(190, 70, 66)` | Logo symbol, accent elements, highlights, CTAs |
| **Warm Beige** | `#F7F1EE` | `rgb(247, 241, 238)` | Primary background, page fill |
| **Dark Charcoal** | `#3E3737` | `rgb(62, 55, 55)` | Footer backgrounds, dark sections, contrast areas |
| **Soft Teal** | `#D5EBEA` | `rgb(213, 235, 234)` | CTA section backgrounds, feature highlights |

### Text Colors

| Name | Hex | RGB | Usage |
|------|-----|-----|-------|
| **Primary Text** | `#333333` | `rgb(51, 51, 51)` | All body text, headings (NOT pure black) |
| **Secondary Text** | `#7C7C7C` | `rgb(124, 124, 124)` | Captions, secondary info, metadata |
| **White Text** | `#FFFFFF` | `rgb(255, 255, 255)` | Text on dark backgrounds (charcoal, footer) |

### Extended Palette (from Åge Peterson illustrations)

These colors appear across the brand illustrations (Hero, 150th anniversary, etc.) and can be used as supporting accents in branded content — especially for charts, infographics, diagrams, and decorative elements.

| Name | Hex | RGB | Usage |
|------|-----|-----|-------|
| **Dusty Rose** | `#F0B0B0` | `rgb(240, 176, 176)` | Soft pink accents, warm highlights |
| **Blush Pink** | `#D09090` | `rgb(208, 144, 144)` | Muted pink, secondary accent |
| **Dark Terracotta** | `#905050` | `rgb(144, 80, 80)` | Deeper red-brown, building facades |
| **Steel Blue** | `#7090B0` | `rgb(112, 144, 176)` | Cool blue-grey, clothing, shadows |
| **Forest Green** | `#509070` | `rgb(80, 144, 112)` | Deep teal-green, nature, clothing |
| **Muted Teal** | `#B0D0D0` | `rgb(176, 208, 208)` | Mid-tone teal, fills and backgrounds |
| **Sage Green** | `#D0F0D0` | `rgb(208, 240, 208)` | Pale green, light backgrounds |
| **Warm Cream** | `#F0F0D0` | `rgb(240, 240, 208)` | Lightest warm tone, highlights |

### Usage Rules
- **NEVER use pure black (#000000)** for text. Always use #333333.
- The warm beige (#F7F1EE) is the default background — not white.
- Use the soft teal (#D5EBEA) sparingly for emphasis sections.
- The red (#BE4642) is for accents only — never for large background fills.

---

## 3. Typography

### Font Families

| Role | Font | Fallback | Weight |
|------|------|----------|--------|
| **Headings** | Ferrogrotesk | sans-serif | 400 (Regular) |
| **Body text** | Plus Jakarta Sans | sans-serif | 400 (Regular) |
| **Navigation/Labels** | Plus Jakarta Sans | sans-serif | 400, uppercase, letter-spacing: 0.8px |

### Heading Hierarchy

| Level | Size | Line Height | Letter Spacing | Transform |
|-------|------|-------------|----------------|-----------|
| H1 | 68px | 80px | -0.64px | UPPERCASE |
| H2 | 50px | 60px | -0.48px | UPPERCASE |
| H3 (label) | 16px | 19.2px | 0.8px | UPPERCASE |
| Body | 18px | 28px | normal | none |
| Small/Caption | 14px | normal | 0.8px | UPPERCASE |

### Typography Rules
- Headings are ALWAYS uppercase with Ferrogrotesk.
- Body text uses Plus Jakarta Sans at 18px with generous line-height.
- Navigation and labels use uppercase with 0.8px letter-spacing.
- **If Ferrogrotesk is unavailable**, use a geometric sans-serif (e.g., Montserrat, Inter, or Poppins) as a substitute.
- **If Plus Jakarta Sans is unavailable**, use Inter, Source Sans Pro, or a clean humanist sans-serif.

### For Presentations (PowerPoint/Google Slides)
Since custom fonts may not be available, use these substitutions:

| Role | Preferred | Substitute 1 | Substitute 2 |
|------|-----------|--------------|--------------|
| Headings | Ferrogrotesk | Montserrat (Regular) | Arial (Bold) |
| Body | Plus Jakarta Sans | Inter | Calibri |

---

## 4. Logo

### Logo Components

The Øgreid logo has two parts:

1. **Symbol**: Three red house/building shapes (#BE4642) arranged side by side. These represent the company's heritage in building and developing businesses.
2. **Wordmark**: "ØGREID" in a bold geometric sans-serif typeface (custom). Available in black and white versions.

### Logo Assets

| Asset | Path | Use for |
|-------|------|---------|
| Symbol (PNG) | `logos/symbol.png` | Digital — icon, favicons, small placements |
| Symbol (JPG) | `logos/symbol.jpg` | Digital — when PNG not supported |
| Wordmark Black | `logos/wordmark-black.png` | Light/beige backgrounds |
| Wordmark White | `logos/wordmark-white.png` | Dark backgrounds |
| Logo + clearspace | `logos/logo-with-clearspace.png` | Reference for minimum padding |

### Logo Usage Rules
- Always maintain clear space around the logo (see `logo-with-clearspace.png`).
- On light/beige backgrounds: use the red symbol + black wordmark.
- On dark backgrounds: use the red symbol + white wordmark.
- Never stretch, rotate, or recolor the logo.
- Minimum size: symbol should be at least 20px tall in digital contexts.

---

## 5. Illustrations

Øgreid uses a distinctive illustration style by **Åge Peterson**, characterized by:
- Flat, stylized characters with elongated proportions
- Limited color palette matching the brand colors (red, teal, pink, black, beige)
- Whimsical, storytelling compositions (people working, building, collaborating)
- Mix of detailed scenes and simpler vignettes

### Illustration Assets

Two versions of each illustration exist:
- **`illustrations/`** — Transparent background (preferred for overlays and flexible layouts)
- **`illustrations-bg/`** — With background fill (ready-to-use, no compositing needed)

| Friendly Name | Filename | Use for |
|--------------|----------|---------|
| **Hero** | `hero.png` | Opening slides, hero banners, main visuals |
| **People** | `people.png` | Team pages, "about our people" content |
| **History** | `history.png` | Company history, timeline, heritage content |
| **Humor 1** | `humor-1.png` | Light-hearted moments, culture content |
| **Humor 2** | `humor-2.png` | Alternative humor scene |
| **Collaboration** | `collaboration.png` | "Why work with Øgreid", intro sections |
| **Network** | `network.png` | Connections, partnerships, ecosystem |
| **Sparring** | `sparring.png` | Advisory, mentoring, sparring partner content |
| **Growth & Capital** | `growth-capital.png` | Investment, growth catalysis, funding |

**Example usage:** To add the hero illustration to a slide, use `illustrations/hero.png`.

